HEADWORD: Alum shale
<hw>Al"um shale"</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A variety of shale or
clay slate, containing iron pyrites, the decomposition of which leads to
the formation of alum, which often effloresces on the rock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alum stone</ent>⟦br⟧
